  "prompt": "How much does an average subway franchise make per year?",
  "response": "The average revenue for a Subway franchise can vary significantly based on location, management, and market conditions. However, industry estimates suggest that an average Subway franchise unit in the United States can generate approximately $400,000 to $500,000 in annual revenue.\n\nIt's important to note that this is gross revenue and not profit. After accounting for expenses such as rent, labor, food costs, royalties, marketing fees, and other operational costs, the net profit can be considerably lower. Franchisees often report a profit margin of around 7% to 12%, but this can also vary widely depending on the efficiency of the operation and local economic factors.\n\nProspective franchisees should conduct thorough research and financial analysis, including detailed projections and consultations with existing franchise owners, before making an investment decision.",
